To deploy this app on Heroku, do the following:


Install Heroku Toolbelt: https://toolbelt.herokuapp.com/

$ mkdir newapp
$ cd newapp
$ virtualenv venv --distribute --no-site-packages
$ source venv/bin/activate
$ git clone git://github.com/Urbsly/heroku-ptah.git
$ cd heroku-ptah
$ heroku create --stack cedar
$ heroku addons:add shared-database
$ git push heroku master
$ heroku ps:scale web=1
$ heroku open

Ideally, you would have forked the repository first, and so checked out a writible clone in step five instead of a read-only copy.

Note: this code won't run on your local machine as is. A bit more cleanup is still needed.
